pull.title: Unit Test Fixes
pull.body:
I got tired of test_bitcoin not building, so I touched up #363.
Also added a transaction test which tests derserialization and duplicate txins.

repo.name: bitcoin
repo.description: Bitcoin (dont fork from here, fork from bitcoin/bitcoin)

events.body: Someone needs to test that this builds on OSX first.

events.message:
Fix testing setup

There were some problems with the existing testing setup:

 - Makefile rules for test-file compilation used CFLAGS instead of
   CXXFLAGS in makefile.unix

Add prototype for EvalScript() to script.h

This is needed for the script unit tests.

events.body: Tested on OSX by b4epoche, seems fine

On current head it fails with: 

test/transaction_tests.cpp(22): error in "RealTransaction": Transaction with duplicate txins should be invalid.
**\* 1 failure detected in test suite "uint160"

I wonder why it sayd 'test suite "uint160"', the failed test is in "transaction_tests".

Re: it fails: yes it is supposed to, that is a bug that should be fixed (see #443 for a potential solution).
Re: uint160, yea I tried to figure out why, but I cant seem to see why, maybe someone else can figure that out...In any case thats a fairly minor UI issue and isnt a regression.
I didn't mean to comment on the failure itself, only on the reporting thereof. It's a minor issue, but maybe it means the boost test framework isn't being used correctly.

events.message: Add a file for script tests
Cleanup test suite output to be more useful.

events.body:
OK, updated with better naming...
Not really anything that can be done within boost test to make the output more specific, so just name the AUTO_TEST_CASE well and use BOOST_CHECK_MESSAGE instead of BOOST_CHECK
Merged after rebasing onto pull #443 (commit 4e5d88 -- apologies if that causes anybody pain).
